@startuml sequence
title Slides Pipeline (Drive-only) — Sequence

actor Trainer
participant "PowerPoint (.pptx local)" as PPTX
participant "Google Drive Sync" as GDSync
participant "Slides Daemon\n(slides_daemon.py)" as Daemon
participant "Google Drive PDF Export URL" as GDrive
participant "Published Slides Folder\n(materials/slides)" as Publish
participant "Backend API\n(FastAPI)" as API
participant "Host UI\n(host.js)" as HostUI

== Local Edit ==
Trainer -> PPTX: Edit + Save
PPTX -> GDSync: Local file updated

== Daemon Detects Dirty ==
Daemon -> PPTX: Poll file mtime
Daemon -> Daemon: detect_changed_files()\nmark deck dirty

== Drive Pull Retries ==
loop Every 5s (max 5 minutes)
  Daemon -> GDrive: GET drive_export_url (PDF)
  alt New PDF fingerprint
    GDrive --> Daemon: PDF bytes (%PDF-...)
    Daemon -> Daemon: update last_drive_fingerprint\nclear out_of_sync
    Daemon -> Publish: write target_pdf
    Daemon -> API: POST /api/quiz-status\n(slides list updated)
    API --> HostUI: state/availability refresh
    break
  else Same fingerprint / transient error
    GDrive --> Daemon: unchanged or error
    Daemon -> Daemon: keep retrying (5s cadence)
  end
end

== Timeout Path ==
alt No new fingerprint within 5 minutes
  Daemon -> Daemon: set out_of_sync=true\nstore out_of_sync_message
  Daemon -> API: POST /api/quiz-status (sync status)
  HostUI -> API: GET /api/slides/participant-availability
  API --> HostUI: entries include sync_status=out_of_sync
  HostUI -> HostUI: Show ⚠️ in 📜 tooltip row
end

@enduml
